Floor logarithm of Church binary numbers.
Given A and base B (B â‰¥ 2, A â‰¥ 1),
return floor(log_B(A)).

A Church binary natural (LSB first, no trailing zeros):
  E    = Î»o.Î»i.Î»e.e
  O(x) = Î»o.Î»i.Î»e.o(x(o,i,e))
  I(x) = Î»o.Î»i.Î»e.i(x(o,i,e))
0=E, 1=I(E), 2=O(I(E)), 3=I(I(E)), 5=I(O(I(E))).
A Church Bin folds: I(O(I(E))) = Î»o.Î»i.Î»e.i(o(i(e))).

